faqs:
  - q: "Is luxury vinyl plank truly waterproof?"
    a: "Yes. Quality LVP features a waterproof core that won't swell, warp, or buckle when exposed to moisture. This makes it an excellent choice for kitchens, bathrooms, laundry rooms, and basements — any area where water exposure is a concern."
  - q: "How does LVP compare to hardwood?"
    a: "LVP offers the look of hardwood with superior water resistance and lower cost. Modern LVP is remarkably realistic in appearance and texture. While hardwood can be refinished multiple times, LVP is more durable against scratches, dents, and daily wear — making it ideal for families with kids and pets."
  - q: "How long does luxury vinyl plank flooring last?"
    a: "Quality LVP typically lasts 15-25 years with normal use. Commercial-grade products can last even longer. The wear layer thickness is the key factor — thicker wear layers provide greater durability and longevity."
  - q: "Can LVP be installed over existing flooring?"
    a: "In many cases, yes. LVP can often be installed over existing hard-surface flooring like tile, hardwood, or concrete — as long as the surface is level and in reasonable condition. Ake will assess your current floors during the free estimate."
