<h3 style="font-size:var(--text-lg);font-weight:600;color:var(--text-primary);margin-top:var(--space-2xl);margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">What Affects LVP Installation Cost?</h3>
<p style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.8;margin-bottom:var(--space-md);">LVP is one of the most cost-effective flooring options. Here's what influences your project cost:</p>
<ul style="color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:2;padding-left:var(--space-lg);">
  <li><strong>Wear layer thickness</strong> — Thicker wear layers (20mil+) cost more but last longer</li>
  <li><strong>Product quality</strong> — Premium brands with realistic textures and attached underlayment cost more</li>
  <li><strong>Subfloor prep</strong> — LVP requires a smooth, level surface; leveling adds to scope</li>
  <li><strong>Room transitions</strong> — Multiple rooms and hallways require more precision with trim work</li>
  <li><strong>Existing flooring removal</strong> — Removing old carpet, tile, or wood adds to the project</li>
</ul>
